  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Because RepairQ is cloud-based, we highly recommend disabling your browser password manager when using our application. Leaving a password manager active can cause security risks, including saving the manager's (or another employee's) login details, which could be used for fraudulent use. Auto-fill can interfere with field details in RepairQ settings as well as credit card swipes during the transaction process.</p><p>We have included instructions on how to turn off these features on our commonly used browsers. Click the link below to jump to the related browser settings.</p><ul><li><p><a href=\"#Google\" rel=\"nofollow\">Google Chrome Browser</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"#Firefox\" rel=\"nofollow\">Firefox Browser</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"#Safari\" rel=\"nofollow\">Safari Browser</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"#Microsoft\" rel=\"nofollow\">Microsoft Edge Browser</a></p></li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: We also recommend turning off third-party password managers like LastPass, etc., as these applications have similar effects on browser fields.</p><p /><h2 id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-GoogleGoogleChromeBrowser\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-Google\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"Google\"></span></span>Google Chrome Browser</h2><p /><p>1. On the upper-right corner of the browser, window, click the <strong>Menu button (\u22ee)</strong>. From the drop-down list of options, click <strong>Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Google%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Settings screen, select <strong>Auto-fill</strong> from the left column. From the Auto-fill settings, select <strong>Password</strong> <strong>Manager</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Google%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Password Manager screen, turn <strong>OFF</strong> the options for<strong> Offer to save passwords</strong> and <strong>Auto Sign-in</strong>. Then click the <strong>Back arrow</strong> to go back to Auto-fill settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Google%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. Repeat the same process for <strong>Payment Methods</strong> and<strong> Addresses and more</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Google%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h2 id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-FirefoxFirefoxBrowser\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-Firefox\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"Firefox\"></span></span>Firefox Browser</h2><p /><p>1. On the upper-right corner of the browser, window, click the <strong>Menu button</strong>. From the drop-down list of options, click <strong>Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Firefox%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Settings screen, select <strong>Privacy &amp; Security</strong> from the left column. Scroll down until you get to the Logins and Passwords section and <strong>uncheck the selections for Ask to save logins and passwords for websites</strong> and <strong>Autofill logins and passwords</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Firefox%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. Scroll down to Forms and Autofill and <strong>uncheck Autofill addresses</strong> and <strong>Autofill credit cards</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Firefox%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h2 id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-SafariSafariBrowser\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-Safari\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"Safari\"></span></span>Safari Browser</h2><p /><p>1. On the upper-left corner of the browser window, click <strong>Safari</strong>. From the dropdown options, click <strong>Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"226\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Screenshot%202023-02-03%20at%2011.23.07%20AM.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. In the Settings window, click the <strong>Autofill</strong> <strong>tab</strong>. Under the AutoFill web forms section, uncheck the autofill details.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Screenshot%202023-02-03%20at%2011.42.31%20AM.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h2 id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-MicrosoftMicrosoftEdgeBrowser\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"RepairQTroubleshooting:DisablePasswordManagersandAutofill-Microsoft\"><span class=\"confluence-anchor-link\" id=\"Microsoft\"></span></span>Microsoft Edge Browser</h2><p /><p>1. On the upper-right corner of the browser window, click the <strong>Menu button</strong>. From the drop-down list of options, click <strong>Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"226\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Edge%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"226\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Edge%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Settings page, click <strong>Profiles</strong> on the left column. Under the Your Profile section, click <strong>Personal</strong> <strong>Info</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Edge%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Personal Info page, <strong>toggle OFF the selections for Save and fill basic info, Automatically fill my info on sign up forms, </strong>and <strong>Save and fill custom info</strong>. Then click the <strong>Back arrow</strong> to go back to the Profile settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Edge%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. On the Your Profile page, click <strong>Passwords</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Edge%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>5. On the Passwords page, <strong>Toggle OFF the selections for Offer to save passwords</strong>, <strong>Automatically save passwords</strong>, and <strong>Autofill passwords</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933836386/Edge%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
